Sports Physicals:

Bring your own writing tool to fill out paperwork!

Girls: Thursday, July 23, 2020 @ 5:30 PM at the clinic. Everyone must wear a mask. Only one allowed in the clinic at a time. Paperwork will be filled out in front.

Boys and bus driver’s physicals will be Monday, July 27, 2020 @ 6:00 PM. Everyone must wear a mask and be temperate checked prior to entering the building.

We ask that distancing be implemented at both clinics. Bring something to fill out paperwork with and a parent or guardian to sign forms.

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

David Wion
My name is David Wion, and I am the 18 year-old son of Monte and Anita Wion. I have 3 older siblings Joshua, Kristin, and Kala.

During my time at Seiling Public Schools, I enjoyed participating in football and FFA all four years of my high school career. I was also involved in powerlifting for two years. While in football, I won all district for the 2019 season.

The thing I will miss the most is my high school football team and coach.

After graduation, I plan to attend Southwester College in Winfield, Kansas where I will continue my academic and football career.

post_text:
SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

Riley Tune
My name is Riley Dean Tune, and I am the 18 year-old son of Bob and Amy Tune. I am the grandson of Bill and Marie Tune of Fort Supply, OK and Jack Nichols and the late Brenda Nichols of Fairview, OK. I have 2 older brothers, Brody and Alex Tune and 1 younger sister, Kyndall Tune.

During my time at Seiling Public Schools, I enjoyed participating in basketball, FFA (serving as Chaplin 1 year), FCA, Student Council (serving as class representative for 4 years and secretary 1 year) all four years of my high school career. I was also involved in baseball and football for 3 years and Beta Club for 1 year (serving as secretary 1 year). While in football, I was chosen as All-District Underclassman Defensive End my junior year and All-District Defensive End my senior year. In my junior year, I was chosen as Great Plains Seven All Conference Player for basketball.

The thing I will miss the most is Coach Templin’s class.

After graduation, I plan to attend Northwestern Oklahoma State University in Alva and major in AgriScience.

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

Brya Nyberg
My name is Brya Nyberg, and I am the 18 year-old daughter of Brandon and Brandi Nyberg. I am the granddaughter of Charles and Jeannie Lewallen of Longdale, OK and Janet Nyberg of Riverton, WY. I have 2 older brothers and 1 younger sister.

During my time at Seiling Public Schools, I enjoyed participating in FCA. BETA Club, and Student Council all four years of my high school career. I was also involved in basketball and track. While in basketball, the team won 3 state titles. While in track I was a part of the 800m relay that was titled state champions, and individually got 3rd place in the 400 and 800 meter runs.

The thing I will miss the most is competing as a Lady Cat. Sports has always been a huge part of my life, and I am so thankful I got to be a Lady Cat my whole high school career!

After graduation, I plan to attend Rogers State University and continue running track while studying graphic design.

Wyatt Duke

My name is Wyatt Loyd Duke, and I am the 19 year-old son of Tucker Duke of Seiling, OK and Amanda & Kevin Kornele of Ft. Supply, OK. The thing I will miss the most is hanging out with friends and showing.

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

My name is Dylan Day, and I am the 19-year-old son of Christina and Matthew Day. I am the grandson of the late Dewayne Day and of the late Karen Boucher and of Rita Day of Camargo, OK and Armando Flores of Camargo, OK. I am the great-grandson of Modell and the late Jim Gift of Seiling, OK. I have one older sister, Paidynn, and one younger sister, Presley.

During my time at Seiling Public Schools, I enjoyed participating in basketball all four years of my high school career. I was also involved in FFA and student council. While in basketball, we won numerous championships throughout my four years here at Seiling High School.

The thing I will miss the most is hanging out with my friends everyday.

After graduation, I plan to attend Southwestern Oklahoma State University and major in health sciences as I want to become a personal trainer.

post_text: 2019 Military Appreciation Night at SHS
text: 2019 Military Appreciation Night at SHS

post_text:
Military Appreciation Night & Pink Out

Friday, October 25, 2019

Seiling Public Schools would like to honor all current and past military by inviting them to enter the game for free on Friday, October 25.

When entering, please tell the gate workers of your service. You will be admitted for free and the FCA would like to show a token of their appreciation to you with a goodie bag. Prior to kickoff, the Seiling Wildcats will take part to honor two of their own and all military personnel in the crowd will be asked to stand for recognition while the FCA releases balloons.

Please don’t miss our tribute to those who served. Show up early and join in the celebration.

At halftime, the mini cheerleaders will perform and honor the cancer fighters, survivors, and those whose memories live on in our hearts.

This is a special evening for our school and we hope that we have a great crowd to support the Wildcats and all our honorees.

post_text:
First Day of School:

Buses will be the ONLY vehicles allowed to drive/park south of the school.

All drop offs need to follow traffic north of the old gym, drop off students at the northeast corner of the bus barn, and turn north and exit north of the Ward Center. You may not park in the driving lane area to walk students in. If you would like to walk them into the building, please park in the Ward Center parking lot.

Walkers should enter from the north between the bus barn and the track.

7th-12th will meet in the Commons Area with Mr. Gregory at 8:15 and there will be signs posted for a session rotation throughout the day. All students will have class sponsors accompanying them to sessions.

7th-12th—If you already picked up your YEARBOOK, please bring it if you would like to participate in the yearbook signing session.

If you have not paid for your Chromebook insurance, please bring your money tomorrow as there will be a session for Chromebook checkout as well. Students will receive a Chromebook if it has been paid.

post_text: Alee Hunt is pictured with Dr. Deanna Joseph, the conductor of the 2019 OkMEA High School All-State Chorus. To be selected to this prestigious chorus, Alee earned a very high score in two separate auditions. It is very difficult to be selected to this chorus as a sophomore. Alee competed against singers from schools across the state in classes 2A-6A. She rehearsed and performed with the all-state chorus January 17-19 at the Tulsa Performing Arts Center.

post_text: Ella Hulett is pictured with Henry Leck, the conductor of the 2019 OkMEA Children's All-State Chorus. Ella was selected by audition to the chorus. Students in all school classifications in grades 4-8 competed to be in the choir. This was the 25th Anniversary of the Children's All-State chorus. So, Ella was privileged to meet several composers of the music that was commissioned and performed at the concert.

Seiling Weightlifting Team competed at Regionals today.

Seiling Weightlifter Payton Gregory placed 2nd in the 181 lbs division and will compete at STATE next weekend at El Reno.🥈

Congrats to all of the guys and Coach Gary Manuel for their successes today!

Go Cats!🐾

WILDCATS and LADY CATS are STATE BOUND! 🏆🏀🏆

The elementary students and teachers sent our teams off with an incredible walk through, chanting and cheering the teams on to victory!

Then the school and community came together to cheer and honk the teams out of town! These two teams have the best fan base in Oklahoma! Come out and support them at 3:30 and 8:30 today!

Go Cats!

Thursday, March 1:

There will be a send off in the bus loading zone at approximately 10:15 followed by a honk out!

BOTH teams will be participating.

The bus will travel by the nursing home and up Main on the way out of town. We hope you can all find a spot, make some signs, honk some horns, and give our teams the send off to STATE they deserve! 🏆🏀🏆
